Wall Street stocks opened sharply lower on Thursday, joining a global equity sell-off after Russia launched a special military operation against Ukraine. A few minutes into trading, the Dow Jones Industrial Average was down 2.2 percent at 32,397.35. The broad-based S&P 500 also declined 2.2 percent to 4,134.60, while the tech-rich Nasdaq Composite Index dropped 2.5 percent to 12,711.66. (With input from AFP)